9️⃣ years! 🎉

as a stray rescue, I’ve never known and therefore never acknowledged lulu’s birthday (not even totally sure how old she is, but the influx of gray hair gives a clue 🥲) 

given her health scare and miraculous comeback a couple months ago, I figured a “gotcha day” celebration was long overdue.

it’s been nearly a decade since my chance encounter with a tiny black mutt in a lubbock, texas parking lot. her name is a nod to her hometown. (also, shout out to roommate and auntie @michaelamac1 for being totally chill about the fact I brought a dog home from work that day 😬)

lulu has been my ride or die ever since, living in four cities in four states. friends, boyfriends, and jobs have come and gone but she’s been my constant, my little shadow for nine years’ worth of highs and lows. I don’t remember much but according to my mom, she never left my side when I came home from the hospital after cancer surgery.

we truly don’t deserve dogs 💕 love ya, little lu.

I lost one of my best friends last week. but this post isn’t about loss. it’s about gain, and the immeasurable value one tiny rescue dog brought to my life (others, too.)

lulu was my sweet, tiny shadow for nearly
a third of my life. four cities, four states, countless memories. we traveled the country together. she went viral on tiktok! this 7 lbs mutt lived a richer life than some adults I know. 

if you ever met lulu, you know she was love personified. she was also sassy as hell, and by far one of the weirdest dogs I’ve ever known. we were, simply put, two peas in a pod.

she clung to my side as I recovered from some pretty scary health problems, and years later when the roles reversed, I returned the favor for her. 

lulu came into this world scrounging on the streets of lubbock, texas and spent her final days strolling (literally, in a stroller) nantucket. that’s the american dog dream, baby.

my grief is great, but my gratitude is greater. love ya always, lu 🖤

a very merry cali christmas 🎄☀️

after a much needed holiday reset with some of my favorite people, in one of my favorite places, enjoying some of my favorite things…let’s just say it wasn’t easy to dieGO back to boston.

2023 pulled off a herculean 4th quarter comeback, thanks to this guy 🥂✨ can’t wait to do 2024 with you, @jblock16. ilysm.
